<p>LG dryer repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County runs <strong>$150–480 total</strong> depending on what's wrong. That's the honest range. A door latch is $150. A motor is $480. Most repairs land in the $280–380 range — one failed component, one visit, dryer working the same day. About half our service calls turn out to be minor fixes — loose connections, vent blockages, error code resets — that cost significantly less. This page breaks down exactly what each repair costs and how we price it.</p>
